In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics including the Christmas decorations at the White House, the appointment of Mick Mulvaney as the director of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB), the President's stance on the Access Hollywood tape, the Alabama Senate race, the President's comments about "Pocahontas," the fight against ISIS, and the future of the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA) program. Sanders also addressed questions about the President's use of racial slurs, his views on Al Franken, and the allegations against him.